    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><em>You say a command word and pour a single drop of mercury into the air, which dissipates and forms into a circular, horizontal plane of force, 3 feet in diameter and 1 inch thick, which floats 3 feet above the ground and follows you, acting as a platform to carry you, objects, or other people.</em></p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong> </p><ul><li><p>A floating disk appears in an unoccupied space 5 ft. space of your choice. It can hold up to 500 pounds, is 5 ft. in diameter, and weighs 5 lbs.</p></li><li><p>While you stand on the disk, you gain a flying (floating) speed of 30 ft., but you can't fly more than 5 ft. above the ground.</p></li><li><p>If you move more than 20 feet away from the disk, it follows you so that it remains within 20 feet of you. It can move across uneven terrain, up or down stairs, slopes and the like, but it sinks in water and can't cross an elevation change of 5 feet or more. For example, the disk can't move across a 5-foot-deep pit, nor could it leave such a pit if it was created at the bottom.</p></li><li><p>This spell ends if you become &amp;reference[incapacitated], you cast this spell again, if more than 500 lbs is placed on the disk, or if you move more than 100 feet from the disk. When this spell ends, everything on the disk falls to the ground.</p></li></ul>",
            "chat": "<strong>Utility Spell</strong> </p><ul><li><p>A floating disk appears in an unoccupied space 5 ft. space of your choice. It can hold up to 500 pounds, is 5 ft. in diameter, and weighs 5 lbs.</p></li><li><p>While you stand on the disk, you gain a flying (floating) speed of 30 ft., but you can't fly more than 5 ft. above the ground.</p></li><li><p>If you move more than 20 feet away from the disk, it follows you so that it remains within 20 feet of you. It can move across uneven terrain, up or down stairs, slopes and the like, but it sinks in water and can't cross an elevation change of 5 feet or more. For example, the disk can't move across a 5-foot-deep pit, nor could it leave such a pit if it was created at the bottom.</p></li><li><p>This spell ends if you become &amp;reference[incapacitated], you cast this spell again, if more than 500 lbs is placed on the disk, or if you move more than 100 feet from the disk. When this spell ends, everything on the disk falls to the ground.</p></li></ul>"
        },
